1 (3) [Sections 1 through 6] do not prevent a city, town, or consolidated city-county government from
2 regulating traffic on streets within their jurisdictional boundaries pursuant to 61-12-101 or improving its
3 transportation network, providing that these regulations or improvements do not discriminate against a vehicle
4 with an automated driving system.
5
6 NEW SECTION. Section 5. Department of transportation rulemaking authority. (1) The
7 department of transportation may adopt rules that limit the use of commercial vehicles with automated driving
8 systems in actual or predicted periods of dangerous road conditions.
9 (2) The department of transportation may exempt from limitation commercial vehicles with an
10 automated driving system that are demonstrated to be capable of operating safely during dangerous road
11 conditions.
12 (3) In conjunction with the department of transportation, the department of justice shall consult
13 interested stakeholders prior to proposing rules on vehicles with an automated driving system, such as
14 members of the transportation interim committee and representatives of law enforcement agencies, motor
15 vehicle and insurance industries, drivers, pedestrians, and tribal and local governments.
16
17 NEW SECTION. Section 6. Department of justice rulemaking authority. (1) The department of
18 justice may adopt rules for the use of a vehicle with an automated driving system.
19 (2) In conjunction with the department of transportation, the department of justice shall consult
20 interested stakeholders prior to proposing rules on vehicles with an automated driving system, such as
21 members of the transportation interim committee and representatives of law enforcement agencies, motor
22 vehicle and insurance industries, drivers, pedestrians, and tribal and local governments.
23
24 NEW SECTION. Section 7. Codification instruction. [Sections 1 through 6] are intended to be
25 codified as an integral part of Title 61, and the provisions of Title 61 apply to [sections 1 through 6].
